<div><h3>ENG 1750 - Post-Colonial Literature </h3>  <hr>This course will provide an introduction to post-colonial literature and theory. We will explore how authors confronted colonialism in their respective countries and their representations of the repercussions in a post-colonial world. Over the course of the semester we will read literature from Africa and India, including (but not limited to) Chinua Achebe, Tayeb Salih, Arundhati Roy, and Salman Rushdie.<br><br><strong>Anticipated Terms Offered:</strong> varied<br><br></div>		</td>
